GC/MS means gas chromatograph and mass spectrometer. You cannot hide or mistake anything with these tests. They would literally show any and every drug in your system (if operated by a suitably skilled person). Not only would they be able to differentiate between (say) codeine/morphine/heroin/fentanyl, they could also provide the concentrations extremely accurately.
But doing that shit is fairly expensive. It's used for all sorts of analysis, whether it be compounds in your blood or to work out what compounds you formed in a reaction.
It might save your arse if you really need it, though.
